would cover the whole of this floor,

00:20:55.520 --> 00:20:57.520
that's how big they were.

00:20:57.520 --> 00:20:58.520
They were lovely,

00:20:58.520 --> 00:20:59.520
lots and lots of material,

00:20:59.520 --> 00:21:01.520
lovely dresses,

00:21:01.520 --> 00:21:02.520
and dressing gown,

00:21:02.520 --> 00:21:04.520
but the dresses were always lovely.

00:21:04.520 --> 00:21:06.520
Well made they were.

00:21:06.520 --> 00:21:07.520
And did you get,

00:21:07.520 --> 00:21:08.520
you got a discount, did you?

00:21:08.520 --> 00:21:09.520
Well, no, what it was,

00:21:09.520 --> 00:21:11.520
they would have a sale

00:21:11.520 --> 00:21:13.520
and then you could buy them cheaper then,

00:21:13.520 --> 00:21:14.520
you know what I mean?

00:21:14.520 --> 00:21:15.520
So...

00:21:15.520 --> 00:21:17.520
Sorry, could you, could you...

00:21:17.520 --> 00:21:20.520
Okay, so, sorry, Rita, about that.

00:21:20.520 --> 00:21:21.520
That's okay.

00:21:21.520 --> 00:21:23.520
Let's go back to the same.

00:21:23.520 --> 00:21:24.520
How many times a year then?

00:21:24.520 --> 00:21:26.520
I would say about twice a year,

00:21:26.520 --> 00:21:28.520
but you could buy,

00:21:28.520 --> 00:21:29.520
they'd bring other things

00:21:29.520 --> 00:21:31.520
into the factory as well then,

00:21:31.520 --> 00:21:32.520
you know what I mean,

00:21:32.520 --> 00:21:33.520
I mean that their sheets,

00:21:33.520 --> 00:21:34.520
pillar slips,

00:21:34.520 --> 00:21:36.520
and you always had a good sale,

00:21:36.520 --> 00:21:37.520
it was worth buying,

00:21:37.520 --> 00:21:38.520
they were lovely clothes,

00:21:38.520 --> 00:21:39.520
really nice clothes,

00:21:39.520 --> 00:21:40.520
and their sheets,

00:21:40.520 --> 00:21:42.520
I mean, everybody that got married,

00:21:42.520 --> 00:21:43.520
they gave them hardex sheets

00:21:43.520 --> 00:21:44.520
for the wedding present,

00:21:44.520 --> 00:21:46.520
and they lasted years,

00:21:46.520 --> 00:21:47.520
they were lovely.

00:21:47.520 --> 00:21:49.520
Yeah, so, you know,

00:21:49.520 --> 00:21:50.520
was the factory,

00:21:50.520 --> 00:21:52.520
was it a kind of nice place to,

00:21:52.520 --> 00:21:53.520
what I mean is,

00:21:53.520 --> 00:21:55.520
sounds as if you had a lovely time then,

00:21:55.520 --> 00:21:56.520
you liked the work.

00:21:56.520 --> 00:21:59.520
Building-wise and facility-wise,

00:21:59.520 --> 00:22:01.520
was it a nice environment

00:22:01.520 --> 00:22:02.520
to work in?

00:22:02.520 --> 00:22:03.520
Yes, yes,

00:22:03.520 --> 00:22:05.520
because we had a lovely canteen,

00:22:05.520 --> 00:22:07.520
I mean, I think it might have been,

00:22:07.520 --> 00:22:08.520
in our days,

00:22:08.520 --> 00:22:09.520
the modern ones,

00:22:09.520 --> 00:22:10.520
you know what I mean,

00:22:10.520 --> 00:22:12.520
because we had a lovely big canteen,

00:22:12.520 --> 00:22:13.520
nice toilets,

00:22:13.520 --> 00:22:15.520
a place to put your bike,

00:22:15.520 --> 00:22:18.520
so, you know, I think, yes,

00:22:18.520 --> 00:22:20.520
the factory was really good.

00:22:20.520 --> 00:22:22.520
Did you think they were good employers?

00:22:22.520 --> 00:22:23.520
Yes, I did, yes,

00:22:23.520 --> 00:22:25.520
they were very good, yes.

00:22:25.520 --> 00:22:32.520
How many of you worked there?

00:22:32.520 --> 00:22:33.520
Have you got any idea?

00:22:33.520 --> 00:22:34.520
Oh, I don't know,

00:22:34.520 --> 00:22:36.520
because there was a bowl, I see.

00:22:36.520 --> 00:22:39.520
There's got to be a few hundred,

00:22:39.520 --> 00:22:43.520
because there was 24 on each bench,

00:22:43.520 --> 00:22:45.520
and that's the sewing part,

00:22:45.520 --> 00:22:47.520
and there must have been

00:22:47.520 --> 00:22:53.520
about 8, 6, 8, 10 in the bench,

00:22:53.520 --> 00:22:54.520
10 benches,

00:22:54.520 --> 00:22:57.520
then they had a row of people doing samples,

00:22:57.520 --> 00:23:00.520
then they had people doing the hand sewing,

00:23:00.520 --> 00:23:01.520
like I showed you,

00:23:01.520 --> 00:23:03.520
then people are cut out,

00:23:03.520 --> 00:23:05.520
then there's packers,

00:23:05.520 --> 00:23:08.520
there was people that had done overlocking,

00:23:08.520 --> 00:23:10.520
people that had done zips,

00:23:10.520 --> 00:23:13.520
so I'd say a few hundred easily.

00:23:13.520 --> 00:23:16.520
And you worked that out, didn't you,

00:23:16.520 --> 00:23:18.520
quite a lot, really.

00:23:18.520 --> 00:23:20.520
That was a lot of people to lose their jobs,

00:23:20.520 --> 00:23:21.520
wasn't it?

00:23:21.520 --> 00:23:22.520
Oh, yes, it was,

00:23:22.520 --> 00:23:24.520
everybody was really upset,

00:23:24.520 --> 00:23:26.520
because we were all friends,

00:23:26.520 --> 00:23:27.520
you know what I mean?

00:23:27.520 --> 00:23:29.520
So it was upsetting.

00:23:29.520 --> 00:23:31.520
Yeah, yeah.

00:23:35.520 --> 00:23:37.520
Oh, sorry.

00:23:38.520 --> 00:23:42.520
Were there married women working there?

00:23:42.520 --> 00:23:45.520
Yes, yes, there were a few married women there,

00:23:45.520 --> 00:23:47.520
and as I say, some of us got married.

00:23:47.520 --> 00:23:51.520
As I said, Sheila and Ash married Peter,

00:23:51.520 --> 00:23:53.520
Peter, who was the engine,

00:23:53.520 --> 00:23:56.520
looked after the machines, you know.

00:23:56.520 --> 00:23:59.520
Yeah, and did you get married when you were there?

00:23:59.520 --> 00:24:01.520
Yes, I did, yes, yes.

00:24:01.520 --> 00:24:04.520
What year did you get married?

00:24:04.520 --> 00:24:05.520
1959.

00:24:05.520 --> 00:24:06.520
Right.

00:24:06.520 --> 00:24:09.520
1959 I got married, yes.

00:24:09.520 --> 00:24:11.520
Were you encouraged to go to night school

00:24:11.520 --> 00:24:12.520
or anything when you were there?

00:24:12.520 --> 00:24:14.520
No, we never had, nothing like,

00:24:14.520 --> 00:24:16.520
well, I didn't anyway.

00:24:16.520 --> 00:24:19.520
Well, you didn't need to with sewing.

00:24:19.520 --> 00:24:21.520
Obviously, people in the office perhaps did,

00:24:21.520 --> 00:24:23.520
you know, because they had different views

00:24:23.520 --> 00:24:25.520
and different things.

00:24:25.520 --> 00:24:27.520
Yes, yes.

00:24:27.520 --> 00:24:32.520
And can you remember how much you were paid a week?

00:24:32.520 --> 00:24:35.520
Or a month, or a week, was it?

00:24:35.520 --> 00:24:37.520
I think it was £2 something.

00:24:37.520 --> 00:24:39.520
If I'd have thought of it,

00:24:39.520 --> 00:24:41.520
I could have looked for my payslip.

00:24:41.520 --> 00:24:45.520
I think it was £2 something, £2...

00:24:46.520 --> 00:24:48.520
£7.60 something like that, I'm not quite sure.

00:24:48.520 --> 00:24:50.520
It wasn't a lot.

00:24:50.520 --> 00:24:52.520
You know, when I say to my grandchildren about it,

00:24:52.520 --> 00:24:54.520
they can't believe it.

00:24:54.520 --> 00:24:57.520
It was about £2 something, I think it was,

00:24:57.520 --> 00:24:59.520
which was good money to us and them.

00:24:59.520 --> 00:25:01.520
Days in, it was a job.

00:25:01.520 --> 00:25:05.520
Well, I was going to ask, how did that feel in the, you know?

00:25:05.520 --> 00:25:07.520
We were quite happy with that.

00:25:07.520 --> 00:25:09.520
It was fine, it was fine.

00:25:09.520 --> 00:25:11.520
And was it piecework or was it...?

00:25:11.520 --> 00:25:13.520
No, no, I didn't go on piecework, no, no.

00:25:13.520 --> 00:25:16.520
Some of the girls did, the ones that done the samples,

00:25:16.520 --> 00:25:21.520
they did, but ours was just a wage, like, you know what I mean?

00:25:21.520 --> 00:25:23.520
You just did your job every day.

00:25:23.520 --> 00:25:27.520
And did you say you still got a wage slip?

00:25:27.520 --> 00:25:30.520
I'd have somewhere, but I'd have to find it.

00:25:30.520 --> 00:25:33.520
I'm sure it was £2 down the yard.

00:25:33.520 --> 00:25:35.520
Right, OK.

00:25:35.520 --> 00:25:38.520
And did you have a pay rise when you were there at all?

00:25:40.520 --> 00:25:43.520
I can't remember, to be honest with you.

00:25:43.520 --> 00:25:45.520
I'm not sure.

00:25:45.520 --> 00:25:47.520
I should imagine he would have had.

00:25:47.520 --> 00:25:50.520
Not much, though, I don't think, because he don't have...

00:25:50.520 --> 00:25:52.520
I can't remember having one.

00:25:54.520 --> 00:25:56.520
Right, OK, that's great.

00:25:58.520 --> 00:26:01.520
Were you all paid the same, do you think?

00:26:01.520 --> 00:26:04.520
Oh, yes, we were all paid the same, yes, yes.

00:26:04.520 --> 00:26:05.520
So everything felt quite...

00:26:05.520 --> 00:26:08.520
Apart from the pieceworkers, obviously, you know?

00:26:08.520 --> 00:26:10.520
Oh, there were some people on piecework, weren't there?

00:26:10.520 --> 00:26:13.520
Yes, yes, they used to do the samples and that, you know?

00:26:13.520 --> 00:26:16.520
But everybody else got paid the same.

00:26:16.520 --> 00:26:21.520
Even the ones with the pressing, you know,

00:26:21.520 --> 00:26:24.520
with the iron doing the pressing of the seams.

00:26:24.520 --> 00:26:26.520
And the cutters out as well?

00:26:26.520 --> 00:26:28.520
I would think so, yes.

00:26:29.520 --> 00:26:31.520
What did you spend your wages on?

00:26:31.520 --> 00:26:34.520
Oh, what did I spend my wages on?

00:26:34.520 --> 00:26:38.520
Well, as I said, for our dinner dance,

00:26:38.520 --> 00:26:42.520
we went and bought these special shoes with all glitter on,

00:26:42.520 --> 00:26:44.520
I remember saving up for that.

00:26:44.520 --> 00:26:47.520
And we had this first evening gown, you know,

00:26:47.520 --> 00:26:51.520
with the big skirts and that, and we had our hair done special.

00:26:51.520 --> 00:26:55.520
But we weren't like the girls today, like it,

00:26:55.520 --> 00:26:56.520
they want to buy everything.

00:26:56.520 --> 00:26:58.520
We didn't do that, we were pretty good.

00:26:58.520 --> 00:27:02.520
I saved a bit, I never went mad, you know what I mean?

00:27:03.520 --> 00:27:04.520
Because I never...

00:27:04.520 --> 00:27:06.520
I only went to a youth club,

00:27:06.520 --> 00:27:09.520
which that's where I met my husband when I was 15.

00:27:09.520 --> 00:27:14.520
But that's all I went because I met him and I didn't go far.

00:27:14.520 --> 00:27:17.520
If he was on leave, we'd go to the cinema, you know,

00:27:17.520 --> 00:27:19.520
we'd go into town for the cinema.

00:27:19.520 --> 00:27:24.520
And as I say, we'd go to the fireworks display with the Horixes.

00:27:24.520 --> 00:27:26.520
Obviously, you'd be buying things then,

00:27:26.520 --> 00:27:29.520
you'd go on the shows and whatever, but that's all.

00:27:29.520 --> 00:27:33.520
We never spent like they do today, you know what I mean?

00:27:33.520 --> 00:27:36.520
Do you remember how much the cinema was in those days?

00:27:36.520 --> 00:27:41.520
I'm not sure, it was two and six, it was one and six and two and six, I think.

00:27:43.520 --> 00:27:45.520
That seems to ring a bell, and they're shilling.

00:27:46.520 --> 00:27:48.520
Shilling two and six, yes.

00:27:48.520 --> 00:27:51.520
One and nine, see, I'm just thinking of the prices now.

00:27:51.520 --> 00:27:53.520
You've got me thinking now.

00:27:56.520 --> 00:27:59.520
Where did you go? Where did you go usually?

00:27:59.520 --> 00:28:01.520
Did you go to one special cinema?

00:28:01.520 --> 00:28:04.520
Well, when my husband was on leave, we'd always go into town,

00:28:04.520 --> 00:28:07.520
as we call it, into Cardiff, like into town.

00:28:07.520 --> 00:28:10.520
And we'd see whatever film was on,

00:28:10.520 --> 00:28:13.520
and we'd go and see The Empire or The Old Year,

00:28:13.520 --> 00:28:15.520
one of those we'd go to.

00:28:15.520 --> 00:28:18.520
I mean, we had a cinema up the road here, which was the Ninian cinema,

00:28:18.520 --> 00:28:22.520
which I only went when my children were,

00:28:22.520 --> 00:28:25.520
when I had my children for my night out,

00:28:25.520 --> 00:28:28.520
my husband had minded children, I'd go with my friend,

00:28:28.520 --> 00:28:30.520
and we'd go and watch a film.

00:28:30.520 --> 00:28:32.520
That's all up the Nin, we used to call it then.

00:28:32.520 --> 00:28:34.520
But no, we only went into town.

00:28:34.520 --> 00:28:38.520
And what we used to do in M-days, we used to call it window shopping,

00:28:38.520 --> 00:28:41.520
because they never had the shutters then, did they?

00:28:41.520 --> 00:28:44.520
So we'd walk around looking in all the shop windows,

00:28:44.520 --> 00:28:48.520
thinking, oh, I'd like that, oh, yes, and whatever.

00:28:48.520 --> 00:28:51.520
But we didn't spend much money in M-days.

00:28:51.520 --> 00:28:53.520
Did you go into town by bus?

00:28:53.520 --> 00:28:56.520
Yes, we went in on the bus, yes, yes.

00:28:56.520 --> 00:28:59.520
Of course, ten o'clock, when the film had finished,

00:28:59.520 --> 00:29:03.520
everybody would be standing up, because they always played the queen then,

00:29:03.520 --> 00:29:05.520
and you'd be waiting for it to finish,

00:29:05.520 --> 00:29:08.520
because you'd have to run and catch your bus.

00:29:10.520 --> 00:29:14.520
Did you share the wages with your family?

00:29:14.520 --> 00:29:16.520
Did you pay your mum anything?

00:29:16.520 --> 00:29:19.520
I did give my mother, mummy, I think it was five shillings,

00:29:19.520 --> 00:29:21.520
something like that, I can't remember, but offhand,

00:29:21.520 --> 00:29:24.520
it might have been about five shillings, I think.

00:29:24.520 --> 00:29:27.520
Oh, yes, you've talked about the perks.

00:29:27.520 --> 00:29:29.520
Can I just ask you about trade unions?

00:29:29.520 --> 00:29:31.520
Were there any trade unions?

00:29:31.520 --> 00:29:33.520
There was a union, yes, there was a union,

00:29:33.520 --> 00:29:37.520
and we all had to join it, we were all joined the union anyway.

00:29:37.520 --> 00:29:39.520
Do you remember what the union was?

00:29:39.520 --> 00:29:41.520
No, I can't remember, no.

00:29:41.520 --> 00:29:46.520
Because when it was, that's how I said about it being cold,

00:29:46.520 --> 00:29:49.520
it had to be a certain temperature,

00:29:49.520 --> 00:29:52.520
because the factory was such a big place,

00:29:52.520 --> 00:29:55.520
because that was to do with the unions,

00:29:55.520 --> 00:29:58.520
they said we had to be at a certain thing.

00:29:58.520 --> 00:30:01.520
I can't remember exactly what it was,

00:30:01.520 --> 00:30:04.520
that's all I can remember about the unions.

00:30:04.520 --> 00:30:07.520
So there were no disputes or anything?

00:30:07.520 --> 00:30:09.520
No, no, no.

00:30:09.520 --> 00:30:12.520
And did you feel fairly treated?

00:30:12.520 --> 00:30:14.520
Yes, I did, yes.

00:30:14.520 --> 00:30:18.520
Did you have to wear a certain uniform for work?

00:30:18.520 --> 00:30:20.520
No, no.

00:30:20.520 --> 00:30:22.520
So you could just wear...

00:30:22.520 --> 00:30:25.520
All the clothes, yes, whatever you wanted to, yes.

00:30:25.520 --> 00:30:26.520
And whatever you wanted?

00:30:26.520 --> 00:30:28.520
Yes, whatever, yes.

00:30:28.520 --> 00:30:30.520
They were quite lax, you know, not lax,

00:30:30.520 --> 00:30:32.520
but so long as you didn't go in and...

00:30:32.520 --> 00:30:35.520
Yes, silly clothes, yes, yes.

00:30:35.520 --> 00:30:36.520
Right, right.

00:30:36.520 --> 00:30:40.520
And do you think, do you feel the work was dangerous in any way?

00:30:40.520 --> 00:30:41.520
No, no.

00:30:41.520 --> 00:30:44.520
I mean, I did so when I was first learning,

00:30:44.520 --> 00:30:47.520
like you're saying, I had the needle right through my finger.

00:30:47.520 --> 00:30:49.520
Do you know what I mean?

00:30:49.520 --> 00:30:51.520
Well, you've just got to learn, haven't you,

00:30:51.520 --> 00:30:52.520
and you just stop,

00:30:52.520 --> 00:30:54.520
and then they pull the needle out then for you,

00:30:54.520 --> 00:30:56.520
do you know what I mean?

00:30:56.520 --> 00:30:58.520
But they had good first aid as well,

00:30:58.520 --> 00:31:00.520
I mean, I've got to be fair.

00:31:00.520 --> 00:31:02.520
But one time I was running across,

00:31:02.520 --> 00:31:04.520
which I shouldn't have done when it was a break,

00:31:04.520 --> 00:31:06.520
and it was raining, not like the leaves are now,

00:31:06.520 --> 00:31:08.520
and I just ran across the door,

00:31:08.520 --> 00:31:10.520
and it was raining, not like the leaves are now,

00:31:10.520 --> 00:31:14.520
and I slipped and fell on the back of my head and knocked myself out.

00:31:14.520 --> 00:31:16.520
Well, then they took me in the room there,

00:31:16.520 --> 00:31:18.520
and I was there for a while,

00:31:18.520 --> 00:31:20.520
but I've got to be fair, they had good first aid.

00:31:20.520 --> 00:31:22.520
They did, yes.

00:31:23.520 --> 00:31:27.520
It often makes me think it was more modern nowadays to what I...

00:31:27.520 --> 00:31:28.520
Do you know what I mean?

00:31:28.520 --> 00:31:30.520
To some of the factories, you know?

00:31:31.520 --> 00:31:33.520
Yes, yes.

