And did you get any overtime, stuff like that?

00:36:16.520 --> 00:36:23.520
Sometimes, if they were rushing on her, they wanted certain things out, sometimes you would.

00:36:23.520 --> 00:36:26.520
You might have to work an hour or so, that's all.

00:36:26.520 --> 00:36:32.520
But not very often. It was mostly because there were so many people there, it was then pretty good.

00:36:36.520 --> 00:36:40.520
And did you have a holiday allowance with pay?

00:36:40.520 --> 00:36:44.520
Yes, I think we had holiday pay.

00:36:45.520 --> 00:36:47.520
Do you remember how much you had in a year?

00:36:47.520 --> 00:36:49.520
Oh, I can't remember, no.

00:36:53.520 --> 00:36:55.520
And bank holidays, stuff like that?

00:36:55.520 --> 00:36:58.520
Yes, we had bank holidays, yes, we had them off.

00:37:00.520 --> 00:37:09.520
Did the factory, did you have sort of different holidays, or was it some factories, especially if the vans were different?

00:37:09.520 --> 00:37:11.520
We used to close down, didn't we, yes.

00:37:11.520 --> 00:37:12.520
Did that happen?

00:37:12.520 --> 00:37:15.520
I'm trying to think now, I can't think now, were did it close down?

00:37:17.520 --> 00:37:20.520
I can't really remember, to be honest.

00:37:23.520 --> 00:37:27.520
Okay. And did you used to go on holidays?

00:37:28.520 --> 00:37:35.520
No, well, no, not really, because in those days you didn't really go on holidays, we didn't.

00:37:35.520 --> 00:37:46.520
We didn't, we'd have, when I was at the girls to go on day trips, you know, on the buses, but when we were married, we never, because my husband was in the army, so we didn't go on holidays.

00:37:50.520 --> 00:38:00.520
I would go down with his Nana, that's right, we went down to Puthcall for a week in the caravan. That's the one time that we can say that we had a week's holiday, you know.

00:38:01.520 --> 00:38:02.520
And when was that?

00:38:02.520 --> 00:38:04.520
I don't know, God years.

00:38:04.520 --> 00:38:05.520
A couple of years after you were married?

00:38:05.520 --> 00:38:07.520
Before we were married, we went down there.

00:38:07.520 --> 00:38:08.520
Oh, before?

00:38:08.520 --> 00:38:14.520
Yes, we went down in Spetsbyn, because she wanted to go and we went with her for company, so she could have the caravan, you know.

00:38:17.520 --> 00:38:25.520
Great. And were you allowed days off for personal reasons, like funerals or things like that?

00:38:25.520 --> 00:38:40.520
I can't remember having days, well when you're younger you don't, you know, there's no funerals really, unless it's immediate family, which I was okay, I did never have that time off for funerals, no. Whether they did, I don't know.

00:38:41.520 --> 00:38:49.520
Yeah, so you can't remember like having to forego a day's pay for having a day off for personal reasons or anything like that?

00:38:49.520 --> 00:38:50.520
No, no.

00:38:50.520 --> 00:39:01.520
Okay. So you know we were talking about these dinner dances, fantastic, and were they organised by the company or by the workers?

00:39:01.520 --> 00:39:03.520
The company organised them.

00:39:03.520 --> 00:39:07.520
And did you pay for those or did the company pay for those?

00:39:08.520 --> 00:39:23.520
Do you know, I can't remember, I don't know whether they paid, because friends came, obviously they would have had to pay the friends. Whether we paid or not, I can't really remember. But they were, you know, in them days it was a proper dinner dance, it was lovely, you know.

00:39:25.520 --> 00:39:31.520
You've talked about the music, it was like a rock and roll, were they like local bands who played?

00:39:31.520 --> 00:39:33.520
Yes, it was, they usually had a live band there.

00:39:34.520 --> 00:39:36.520
Do you remember any of them?

00:39:36.520 --> 00:39:40.520
No, not really. It's a long time back now.

00:39:41.520 --> 00:39:43.520
And do you remember what you had to eat then?

00:39:43.520 --> 00:39:55.520
Oh gosh, you're joking, no. I know it would be like you'd have soup with you and you'd have your meal in your sweetener. And I don't know if we had after eight minutes and things like that, I don't think we did then.

00:39:55.520 --> 00:40:07.520
It was a three course meal, do you know what I mean? It was a proper dinner, as I say, a dinner dance, which would have to be done properly, you know what I mean?

00:40:07.520 --> 00:40:09.520
And how many times a year would that be?

00:40:09.520 --> 00:40:12.520
Only, I was a Christmas one, I was a Christmas one now.

00:40:18.520 --> 00:40:23.520
So, you were allowed to take people?

00:40:23.520 --> 00:40:26.520
Yes, friends wanted to come here, but they could come as well.

00:40:27.520 --> 00:40:28.520
Right, so who did you take?

00:40:29.520 --> 00:40:31.520
My husband, they took my husband with me.

00:40:32.520 --> 00:40:33.520
Every time?

00:40:33.520 --> 00:40:34.520
Yes.

00:40:34.520 --> 00:40:36.520
Not sort of local friends?

00:40:37.520 --> 00:40:42.520
No, because my main friend, Marion, she worked there anyway, she was in the office.

00:40:43.520 --> 00:40:45.520
Oh yeah, you said, yeah.

00:40:45.520 --> 00:40:57.520
Is there any one event that you remember from your time in the factory, like a visit by a famous person or anything like that?

00:40:58.520 --> 00:41:12.520
Well, the only famous person that I know is, I told you, was Lorna Leslie, because she worked with us, you know, and she was a scream, she'd have us all singing, she was always laughing, always laughing, she was, she was really good.

00:41:12.520 --> 00:41:15.520
And what did she go on to do then?

00:41:16.520 --> 00:41:21.520
Well, I don't know, because we all split, once the factory closed, that was it, so everybody went.

00:41:22.520 --> 00:41:29.520
But then she was going to, she started to sing then under Lorna Leslie, that was her name, that was her, that's what she was doing, singing.

00:41:30.520 --> 00:41:32.520
So what happened after that, I don't know.

00:41:34.520 --> 00:41:37.520
You don't remember any, does she bring out any records or anything?

00:41:37.520 --> 00:41:44.520
Oh, she did shows, I think, she done concerts, she might, obviously she must have done records, because she done shows, you know.

00:41:45.520 --> 00:41:46.520
And you didn't go and see her?

00:41:47.520 --> 00:41:48.520
No, no, no.

00:41:49.520 --> 00:41:50.520
Okay, great.

