I went with my, there was a bus, I went with my husband, and we went to the Fire and Porthogol.

00:42:51.520 --> 00:42:52.520
It was a great night out, you know.

00:42:53.520 --> 00:42:58.520
You know, the girls would take their boyfriends and we'd go to Porthogol and watch the fireworks and go on the shows.

00:42:59.520 --> 00:43:00.520
It was just a great night out, you know.

00:43:01.520 --> 00:43:03.520
And so was that a kind of annual event on?

00:43:04.520 --> 00:43:05.520
Yes, it was, yes, yes.

00:43:06.520 --> 00:43:07.520
On Bonfire Night?

00:43:08.520 --> 00:43:09.520
Yes.

00:43:10.520 --> 00:43:17.520
Okay, great. So we'll go on then, Rita, to, so you left Horrocks. What year was it again?

00:43:17.520 --> 00:43:24.520
What do we say now? Those sixties, maybe six, yes, 59, 60. It was after I got married.

00:43:25.520 --> 00:43:26.520
Right.

00:43:27.520 --> 00:43:28.520
Yes, that's what you said.

00:43:29.520 --> 00:43:41.520
I think it was now. And then, like I said, we had to go to this place on Wesker Street and eventually I found a job in West Canal Wharf.

00:43:41.520 --> 00:43:47.520
Now, after working in Horrocks, such a lovely factory, I couldn't believe it.

00:43:48.520 --> 00:43:58.520
Because you went in this little door, and as you went in, there was all coal at the back, and then you went up these stairs,

00:43:59.520 --> 00:44:08.520
and when you got up to the stairs then, you turned right, and there was this room with, there was only two machines,

00:44:08.520 --> 00:44:17.520
and then when I started, there would have been three. The boss, Mr Spencer, and one boy, a great boy, was cutting out.

00:44:18.520 --> 00:44:26.520
And we were making school satchels, handbags, and sometimes we'd make purses, but mostly it was school satchels.

00:44:27.520 --> 00:44:35.520
And there was three girls on the machines, and it was big machines, heavy machines, same as we had in Horrocks, but a bit stronger.

00:44:35.520 --> 00:44:42.520
But you had an oily rag, you had to oil a seam, and then machine it.

00:44:43.520 --> 00:44:52.520
It was okay, I was nice girls, and we used to chat, and all that business, but after working in Horrocks, it was entirely different,

00:44:53.520 --> 00:45:00.520
because we'd have a break, he'd turn the machines off, and the boss would make the tea, and then we'd have this bowl,

00:45:00.520 --> 00:45:08.520
and everybody would wash their hands in this bowl to have a cup of tea, and whatever, the same bowl.

00:45:09.520 --> 00:45:21.520
And then this one time, I picked up imbatagol from the oil, I must have had a pimple and scratched in, I had imbatagol on my face, it was dreadful.

00:45:21.520 --> 00:45:33.520
I told the boss, that's fine, he said, we've still all washed in this bowl and still use the same towel, which these days you just can't believe.

00:45:34.520 --> 00:45:46.520
But it was okay, I enjoyed it there, but then, as I said, I left there then, because my husband was in Germany, and I went to Germany to live then, that's when I finished work completely.

00:45:47.520 --> 00:45:51.520
So, can I just ask you, was the factory called Spencer's?

00:45:52.520 --> 00:46:02.520
I'm not sure what it was called, but the boss's name was Mr Spencer, but he used to make school satchels and hambags, purses, but it wasn't a big place, as I said,

00:46:03.520 --> 00:46:14.520
there was only three machiners and a boy cutting out on him, so there was only five of us in this, which was the factory, but, you know, I mean, there was a lot to be desired after Horrocks's.

00:46:14.520 --> 00:46:23.520
I mean, there was no restroom, no first aid or anything, I mean, I can't even remember where the toilet was, to be honest with you.

00:46:24.520 --> 00:46:30.520
You know what I mean, you just can't believe it, he just wore this pinny, white pinny, you just can't believe it.

00:46:31.520 --> 00:46:33.520
Oh, they got away with it in them days.

00:46:34.520 --> 00:46:42.520
There was other factories round there, which was, they used to call it the butter factory, and there was another place that used to do bras and knickers.

00:46:42.520 --> 00:46:52.520
I tried to get in there, but of course most of our girls had already got in there, so that was my next, and I wanted a sewing job, you know, so that's why I worked there.

00:46:53.520 --> 00:46:58.520
Yeah, so was the water in this bowl, was it hot at least?

00:46:59.520 --> 00:47:04.520
Yeah, well he'd boil the kettle and put water in and add cold, so we'd all use the same bowl of water.

00:47:05.520 --> 00:47:08.520
So did it take you a while to get rid of this impotigo?

00:47:08.520 --> 00:47:12.520
Oh yes, it did take me a while, because it was horrible it was.

00:47:13.520 --> 00:47:19.520
But I still went to work, see, I told him, but he said, no that's fine, I still wash my hands in the bowl.

00:47:20.520 --> 00:47:25.520
You can't believe it, can you? You just can't believe it, but there you are.

00:47:26.520 --> 00:47:29.520
So who did he supply with these?

00:47:30.520 --> 00:47:34.520
I'd be honest with you, I don't know, all they know is I worked there, so I don't know.

00:47:34.520 --> 00:47:39.520
They were school satchels, so whether it was for a shop or, I don't know.

00:47:40.520 --> 00:47:43.520
So how big was the place then?

00:47:44.520 --> 00:47:49.520
Only tiny, it was only just one room, that's all it was.

00:47:50.520 --> 00:48:00.520
As I say, there was three of us on the sewing machines, but there was probably four sewing machines, one table for cutting out,

00:48:00.520 --> 00:48:09.520
and a little table where he was sat, and we'd have a table in the middle to wash our hands, so it wasn't big.

00:48:10.520 --> 00:48:13.520
So how did you feel working there?

00:48:14.520 --> 00:48:20.520
Well I enjoyed working with the girls, but I didn't feel as if I was clean there, do you understand me?

00:48:21.520 --> 00:48:25.520
After working in Horlickses it was entirely different, you know.

00:48:25.520 --> 00:48:28.520
How long were you there then?

00:48:30.520 --> 00:48:35.520
I'm not sure, about 18 months I think, because then I went to Germany.

00:48:36.520 --> 00:48:40.520
Did you keep in touch with any of those girls then?

00:48:41.520 --> 00:48:47.520
No, because the one woman was a lot older than me, and the other girl, no I never.

00:48:47.520 --> 00:48:50.520
Do you remember how much you were paid?

00:48:51.520 --> 00:48:57.520
No, I can't remember, probably about the same, because it was the same as the other girls.

00:48:58.520 --> 00:49:03.520
I was paid £1,000 a month, and I was paid £1,000 a month.

00:49:04.520 --> 00:49:07.520
So you were paid £1,000 a month?

00:49:08.520 --> 00:49:10.520
Yes, £1,000 a month.

00:49:10.520 --> 00:49:12.520
Do you remember how much you were paid?

00:49:13.520 --> 00:49:20.520
No, I can't remember, probably about the same, because it was the same type of wages, one lived in M days.

00:49:21.520 --> 00:49:23.520
I'm not sure to be honest.

00:49:24.520 --> 00:49:29.520
That's what I was going to ask you as well, could you chat there, could you chat and listen to music?

00:49:30.520 --> 00:49:37.520
Yes, we could talk there, of course there was only three of us to chat to, so we used to talk, you know what I mean.

00:49:37.520 --> 00:49:42.520
I didn't enjoy it like I did Horixys, you know, the great atmosphere in Horixys.

00:49:43.520 --> 00:49:45.520
Where did you go for lunch then?

00:49:46.520 --> 00:49:52.520
We just used to stay in a factory and then I didn't ever come home, because it was in town.

