I'm just trying to think what hours they were. It was probably nine till five, but we didn't go out, we stayed in a factory for the hour, you know, just chatting.

00:50:23.520 --> 00:50:24.520
Was there an union there?

00:50:25.520 --> 00:50:26.520
No, no.

00:50:27.520 --> 00:50:30.520
Apart from the impotai, what kind of boss was Mr Spencer?

00:50:30.520 --> 00:50:31.520
He was okay.

00:50:32.520 --> 00:50:33.520
Quite fair?

00:50:34.520 --> 00:50:38.520
He was alright. How can I explain?

00:50:39.520 --> 00:50:50.520
He could get a bit moody on times, but as I said, after working in Horixys, nothing seemed the same, you know what I mean.

00:50:51.520 --> 00:50:57.520
I wasn't as happy there as I was. I mean, I worked there because I needed the money, you know what I mean.

00:50:57.520 --> 00:51:03.520
I got on because they said there were only two other girls to chat to.

00:51:04.520 --> 00:51:13.520
But it wasn't the atmosphere and you weren't laughing and joking like you were in Horixys. It was like a life, but there it was work and that was it. You know what I mean?

00:51:17.520 --> 00:51:21.520
Did you have holidays there? Do you remember?

00:51:21.520 --> 00:51:30.520
I probably did, but I can't really remember because we wouldn't have gone away then, so I'm not sure about that.

00:51:31.520 --> 00:51:35.520
Obviously we had bank holidays and things like that, which they did then.

00:51:38.520 --> 00:51:40.520
And any social life?

00:51:41.520 --> 00:51:48.520
Well, as I said, I used to go to a youth club. That's where I met my husband. I used to go to the cinema.

00:51:48.520 --> 00:51:52.520
But what I mean is there was nothing organised by the school?

00:51:53.520 --> 00:51:57.520
Oh, in the factory? No, nothing at all like Horixys.

00:51:58.520 --> 00:52:06.520
You say you weren't particularly happy there, but were you bored? Was it monotonous?

00:52:06.520 --> 00:52:11.520
Well, I wouldn't say I'm bored because I used to like sewing.

00:52:12.520 --> 00:52:21.520
But I used to get a bit fed up sometimes because there was no laughter and joking. It was just work and doing the same thing.

00:52:22.520 --> 00:52:28.520
He wasn't the happiest person, so it wasn't as nice.

00:52:30.520 --> 00:52:32.520
How did you get to work there then?

00:52:33.520 --> 00:52:34.520
I used to catch the bus.

00:52:34.520 --> 00:52:36.520
Sorry, can you say that again?

00:52:37.520 --> 00:52:38.520
I used to catch the bus to work.

00:52:39.520 --> 00:52:40.520
So no bike into town then?

00:52:41.520 --> 00:52:46.520
No, I'd catch the bus then. The bus on the corner would take me straight to the monument. I'd catch the bus home then.

00:52:47.520 --> 00:52:49.520
What was West Canow off like in those days?

00:52:50.520 --> 00:53:01.520
There was plenty of work there because, like I said, the bus used to be packed going to work and coming home because they'd be going to the place where they made the bras and the knickers, and then there was the butter factory.

00:53:01.520 --> 00:53:09.520
So there was a lot of people finishing work at the same time. You'd all be on the bus. You'd be busy. You'd chat to people on the bus.

00:53:12.520 --> 00:53:14.520
Did you like working in town at all?

00:53:15.520 --> 00:53:18.520
I didn't mind because it wasn't that far.

00:53:23.520 --> 00:53:27.520
So you left because your husband…

00:53:27.520 --> 00:53:47.520
Well, he was stationed in Germany and I was just becoming pregnant then and we went over to Germany to live. So that's why I left. How long he went on after, I don't know the factory. Like I said, it was only a small factory.

00:53:48.520 --> 00:53:50.520
And how long were you in Germany for?

00:53:51.520 --> 00:53:53.520
For 18 months to 2 years.

00:53:53.520 --> 00:53:59.520
I'll just put this off for a minute. I'll just finish off now.

00:54:00.520 --> 00:54:05.520
So did you ever go back and work anywhere else, Rita?

00:54:05.520 --> 00:54:27.520
No. Well, I had three children and then when my youngest was about six or seven, I started in St Paul's School, which used to be the Nash as a dinner lady, and I worked there 38 years. I retired now last Christmas. I've been off this year, but I loved it. I love working with children.

00:54:27.520 --> 00:54:48.520
I think if I'd have had my time over again, like they have all these opportunities today, I would have worked with children because I do like working with children and handicapped children as well. So I think I enjoy doing what I did, but I think after working with children, I think that's what I would have loved to have done.

00:54:48.520 --> 00:54:59.520
Great. Looking back over your life and looking back to Horroxes, what would you say?

00:54:59.520 --> 00:55:18.520
Oh, I enjoyed Horroxes. Don't get me wrong, he was lovely. I did enjoy it. As I say, they looked after their staff and it was a good factory. It was. Now, I do like working with children, but I'm not saying I did enjoy Horroxes. It was really good.

00:55:19.520 --> 00:55:21.520
Brilliant. Thank you very much.

00:55:22.520 --> 00:55:23.520
Thank you.

